3.3 tonnes for Klima's 33rd retirement - I apologize if I take poetic licenses, but we are standing in front of the 6th mass extinction event. Rather than speaking in dollars and derivatives- I choose to use this blockchain to speak to the soul. Because as NFTs have reminded us- even art is an asset class. I would argue it was the first; Art was the asset class that made humans human. Even as hunter gatherers, societies from long ago left us remnants of cave paintings and stone carved statues. And we know they had great value then because we still cherish those artifacts in museums today as they speak to us millennia later. It was song and story that banded us together by more than family tie- well before the written word or sewn seed. One could say human history is a long painted narrative of asset classes- moments of coming together to create many different forms of value: physical, intellectual, or spiritual value. And so today- lets make a new currency together. A new measure of value. Not measured by pieces of silver or decrees of kings. But a currency measured in belief. A shared belief that by working together there can be a bright future for life on the only place we could ever call home. - NaPalm
